<HL>
   ITT Bows to Non-Smokers
</HL>
<DATE>
12/21/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   ITT
</CO>
<IN>
LODGING, HOTELS, MOTELS, LODGES, CAMPGROUNDS (LOD)
</IN>
<LP>
   BOSTON -- ITT Sheraton said it plans to increase the
number of nonsmoking rooms at its hotels in the U.S. and
Canada, in response to increased consumer requests.
   The company, a subsidiary of ITT Corp., New York, said it
will boost the number of nonsmoking rooms to a minimum of
25%, up from 10%.
